    {
      "id": "agent-prompting-contracts-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Minimal Contracts",
      "position": {
        "x": 1180,
        "y": 315
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 430,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Minimal Contracts\n\nTreat this as the v1 implementation contract for future node classes.\n\n`agent`\n- required: `identity`, `role`, `authority`\n- optional: `availableTools`, `owner`, `status`\n- rules: may act only within an attached `contract`; should remain attributable across delegated work\n\n`prompt`\n- required: `instructionBody`, `scope`, `inputs`\n- optional: `version`, `provenance`, `expectedOutput`\n- rules: should preserve prompt lineage; should be referenceable by downstream `observation` and `result` nodes\n\n`tool`\n- required: `name`, `capability`, `invocationBoundary`\n- optional: `failureMode`, `cost`, `latencyClass`\n- rules: invocation should be explicit and inspectable, not implied by prose alone\n\n`contract`\n- required: `allowedActions`, `safetyLimits`, `requiredOutputs`\n- optional: `escalationRule`, `approvalRequirement`, `terminationCondition`\n- rules: bounds what an `agent` may do; should be readable before execution begins\n\n`task`\n- required: `objective`, `status`\n- optional: `owner`, `acceptanceSignal`, `priority`\n- rules: anchors why the run exists; should connect to the initiating `agent` and eventual `result`\n\n`observation`\n- required: `evidencePayload`, `source`, `timestamp`\n- optional: `toolRef`, `confidence`, `artifactRef`\n- rules: records what was seen, not what was concluded; should preserve provenance\n\n`result`\n- required: `outputPayload`, `status`\n- optional: `confidence`, `qualityNote`, `artifactRef`\n- rules: should preserve lineage to the `prompt` and supporting `observation` nodes\n\n`handoff`\n- required: `sender`, `receiver`, `handoffPackage`\n- optional: `unresolvedRisks`, `expectedNextAction`, `deadline`\n- rules: transfers responsibility explicitly; should not erase prior ownership or lineage\n\nCross-type rules:\n- `task -> agent -> prompt -> observation/result -> handoff` is the canonical v1 loop\n- `contract` is the main execution boundary\n- `memory` remains outside the v1 contract\n- `skill` remains uncommitted as a node type",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
