    {
      "id": "agent-prompting-loop-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Canonical Loop",
      "position": {
        "x": 1180,
        "y": -605
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Canonical Loop\n\nA minimal agent run usually looks like:\n\n1. `task`\n2. `agent`\n3. `prompt`\n4. `tool` or direct reasoning\n5. `observation`\n6. `result`\n7. optional `handoff`\n\nThat loop is the main reason this set is worth modeling.\n\nIt turns opaque prompting into an inspectable authored flow.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
            "source": "local",
            "version": ">=0.1.0"
          },
          "views": [
            {
              "key": "markdown",
              "intent": "editor",
              "payload": "editor.web",
              "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
