    {
      "id": "agent-prompting-capabilities-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Substrate Dependency Contract",
      "position": {
        "x": 1210,
        "y": 1305
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 420,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Substrate Dependency Contract\n\nThe v1 nodeset is only real if the substrate can support the following capabilities.\n\n### 1. Prompt authoring and extraction\n- required by: `task`, `agent`, `prompt`\n- minimum viable support:\n  - prompts can be authored as first-class node content\n  - prompt bodies can reference upstream task context\n  - prompt text can be extracted cleanly for execution or review\n- if missing:\n  - `prompt` becomes decorative instead of executable\n\n### 2. Execution visibility\n- required by: `agent`, `tool`, `observation`, `result`\n- minimum viable support:\n  - runs can show active / complete / failed status\n  - tool calls can be surfaced as visible execution steps\n  - results can retain a readable execution trace\n- if missing:\n  - agent runs collapse back into opaque chat or hidden logs\n\n### 3. Lineage and traceability\n- required by: `prompt`, `observation`, `result`, `handoff`\n- minimum viable support:\n  - results can point back to prompts and supporting observations\n  - observations preserve provenance\n  - handoffs preserve who produced what and why\n- if missing:\n  - the graph cannot explain how an output was produced\n\n### 4. Bounded execution and policy enforcement\n- required by: `contract`, `agent`, `tool`\n- minimum viable support:\n  - contracts can be attached to runs or agents\n  - tool access can be restricted by declared bounds\n  - escalation or stop conditions can be represented and inspected\n- if missing:\n  - `contract` becomes advisory text instead of a real boundary\n\n### 5. Handoff and navigation support\n- required by: `handoff`, `task`, `agent`\n- minimum viable support:\n  - a handoff can point to downstream work\n  - delegated work remains navigable from parent work\n  - responsibility transfer is visible rather than implied\n- if missing:\n  - multi-agent work becomes hard to follow and easy to lose\n\n### 6. Summary surfaces for runs\n- required by: `task`, `result`, `handoff`\n- minimum viable support:\n  - task graphs can expose current status and next actions\n  - important outputs can be summarized without opening every node\n  - parent graphs can consume child run summaries\n- if missing:\n  - agent work does not compose well across graphs\n\n### 7. Artifact attachment and references\n- required by: `observation`, `result`\n- minimum viable support:\n  - evidence and outputs can link to files, logs, or external artifacts\n  - references remain inspectable after the run completes\n- if missing:\n  - observations and results lose concrete grounding\n\nImplementation rule:\n- if a required substrate capability is absent, the related node type may still be modeled, but it should be treated as partially supported rather than operational.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
            "source": "local",
            "version": ">=0.1.0"
          },
          "views": [
            {
              "key": "markdown",
              "intent": "editor",
              "payload": "editor.web",
              "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
              "source": "local",
              "version": ">=0.1.0"
            },
            {
              "key": "markdown",
