    {
      "id": "agent-prompting-followup-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Follow-Up Questions",
      "position": {
        "x": 1180,
        "y": 865
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Follow-Up Questions\n\n- When does `memory` become a first-class node instead of prompt/context data?\n- Is `skill` a node, a reusable graph, a contract bundle, or a tool grouping?\n- Which relationships need typed edges rather than plain references?\n- How much execution state belongs on nodes versus external logs?\n- What is the minimum safe handoff contract between agents?",
        "_classBinding": {
